{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO"]]},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TestDBusRef","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"TestDBusRef"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Note that ","type":"text"},{"code":"GTestDBus","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" modifies the user’s environment, calling"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"man:setenv(3)","isActive":true},{"text":". This is not thread-safe, so all ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTestDBus"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"calls should be completed before threads are spawned, or should have"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"appropriate locking to ensure no access conflicts to environment variables"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"shared between "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTestDBus"},{"type":"text","text":" and other threads."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Creating-unit-tests-using-GTestDBus","text":"Creating unit tests using `GTestDBus`","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Testing of D-Bus services can be tricky because normally we only ever run","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"D-Bus services over an existing instance of the D-Bus daemon thus we"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"usually don’t activate D-Bus services that are not yet installed into the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"target system. The "},{"code":"GTestDBus","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" object makes this easier for us by taking care"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of the lower level tasks such as running a private D-Bus daemon and looking"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"up uninstalled services in customizable locations, typically in your source","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"code tree."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The first thing you will need is a separate service description file for the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"D-Bus daemon. Typically a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"services"},{"text":" subdirectory of your ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"tests"},{"type":"text","text":" directory"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is a good place to put this file."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The service file should list your service along with an absolute path to the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"uninstalled service executable in your source tree. Using autotools we would"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"achieve this by adding a file such as ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"my-server.service.in"},{"text":" in the services","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"directory and have it processed by configure."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["[D-BUS Service]","Name=org.gtk.GDBus.Examples.ObjectManager","Exec=`abs_top_builddir`@\/gio\/tests\/gdbus-example-objectmanager-server"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":null},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You will also need to indicate this service directory in your test","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"fixtures, so you will need to pass the path while compiling your"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"test cases. Typically this is done with autotools with an added","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"preprocessor flag specified to compile your tests such as:"}]},{"syntax":null,"type":"codeListing","code":["-DTEST_SERVICES=\\\"\"$(abs_top_builddir)\/tests\/services\"\\\""]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Once you have a service definition file which is local to your source tree,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"you can proceed to set up a GTest fixture using the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTestDBus"},{"type":"text","text":" scaffolding."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An example of a test fixture for D-Bus services can be found"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"here:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/gitlab.gnome.org\/GNOME\/glib\/-\/blob\/HEAD\/gio\/tests\/gdbus-test-fixture.c"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Note that these examples only deal with isolating the D-Bus aspect of your","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"service. To successfully run isolated unit tests on your service you may need","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"some additional modifications to your test case fixture. For example; if your"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"service uses [class","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Settings"},{"text":"] and installs a schema then it is important","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"that your test service not load the schema in the ordinary installed location","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(chances are that your service and schema files are not yet installed, or"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"worse; there is an older version of the schema file sitting in the install","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"location).","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Most of the time we can work around these obstacles using the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"environment. Since the environment is inherited by the D-Bus daemon"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"created by ","type":"text"},{"code":"GTestDBus","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and then in turn inherited by any services the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"D-Bus daemon activates, using the setup routine for your fixture is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"a practical place to help sandbox your runtime environment. For the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"rather typical GSettings case we can work around this by setting","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSETTINGS_SCHEMA_DIR"},{"text":" to the in tree directory holding your schemas","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"in the above "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fixture_setup()"},{"type":"text","text":" routine."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The GSettings schemas need to be locally pre-compiled for this to work. This"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"can be achieved by compiling the schemas locally as a step before running","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"test cases, an autotools setup might do the following in the directory","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"holding schemas:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["    all-am:","            $(GLIB_COMPILE_SCHEMAS) .","","    CLEANFILES += gschemas.compiled"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TestDBusRef","isActive":true},{"text":" type acts as a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTestDBus"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It exposes methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TestDBusProtocol","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" conformance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TestDBusRef","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" only as an "},{"code":"unowned","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" reference to an existing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTestDBus"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}]},{"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TestDBus","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TestDBusRef","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":") if you want to use Automatic Reference Counting for memory management of the underlying "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTestDBus"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A helper class for testing code which uses D-Bus without touching the user’s"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"session bus.","type":"text"}],"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Initializers","generated":true,"title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TestDBusRef\/init(_:)-24tb1","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TestDBusRef\/init(_:)-4bbjt","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TestDBusRef\/init(_:)-6yybc","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TestDBusRef\/init(_:)-8pg18","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TestDBusRef\/init(_:)-gref","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TestDBusRef\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TestDBusRef\/init(constPointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TestDBusRef\/init(flags:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TestDBusRef\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TestDBusRef\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TestDBusRef\/init(mutating:)","do